DeepMetrica Customer Segmentation Analysis - Websites Using Crazy Egg

Tugrul Ozsoy

27 Eylül 2020

1 Introduction

The data we analyzed consisting of the 5,000 websites using the technology of one of the our secondary competitors Crazy Egg. Domain, Website Language, Global and Local Traffic Rank and Number of Referring Domains are the variables. The dataset is exported from hunter.io and enhanced by Alexa Rank tool of SEO Tools for Excel Add-on.

Crazy Egg is one of the strongest technology giving service in heatmaps and session recording to websites.

Here, you can see some visuals about Crazy Egg:

They provide service for almost 100,000 websites across the world. Some of the most leading countries provided after United States, United Kingdom, Canada, Australia are India, Brazil, Germany, and France.

The websites purchased Crazy Egg have verticals mostly like Computer Electronics&Technology, Arts&Entertainment, and Others which can be consisted of News&Media, E-commerce, etc.

Crazy Egg is also very popular among the sites having the most monthly visits around the world as Outbrain, Aajtak, or El Mundo.

2 Data Analyses

2.1 Alexa Ranking of Websites

When we group the 2k websites using Crazy Egg by their Alexa rankings. Alexa rankings which show traffic levels are categorized as:

Very High -> Lower than 5000

High -> Between 5000 and 100000

Medium -> Between 100000 and 250000

Low -> Between 250000 and 500000

Very Low -> Higher than 500000

Since our sample data contains the websites which are in a very large interval of 173-10,304,767 Alexa Global Rank, and total number of elements are only 5K; most of the websites stay as outliers.

With the help of this chart, we can deduce that rather than websites having only high traffic levels, domains having least monthly visits and almost non-traffic at all are also eager to demand this kind of service. They prefer Crazy Egg more than we guess to enhance their UX and increase their traffic and clicks. However, it looks like majority gains no benefit still.

2.2 Referring Domains

When we examine the total number of referring domains in each traffic level group, we observe some deviation due to the reason I have mentioned in the previous chart: missing information. Ideally, it would be expected that the amount of referring domains/backlinks is higher as traffic level gets high.

It is the natural result of the correlation between number of referring domains/backlinks and SEO ranking of a website. However, the issue that very low traffic websites have more referring domains than medium is sourced from missing information again.

2.4 Verticals of Websites

When we look at the verticals of the websites using Crazy Egg technology, we observe that most of them are Internet&Telecom, Technology or Education&Career. To focus on these categories of websites in terms of marketing at first step could be ideal for DeepMetrica.
